      {
        "id": 3956964,
        "name": "Cris Whetstone",
        "username": "Cris_Whetstone",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/cris_whetstone/{size}/404_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-12-23T03:22:19.166Z",
        "cooked": "<p>We did a tasting of suspect bottles back in September. Our somewhat low filled bottle of the '66 Beychevelle was my WOTN. Very classic profile and seemed to be just in the later half of it\u2019s prime. I really didn\u2019t expect it to be that good even from a well filled bottle.</p>",
