      {
        "id": 4164617,
        "name": "Mark Thompson",
        "username": "Mark_Thompson",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/8e8cbc/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2023-09-30T05:14:36.457Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Opened a bottle with similar ullage to Mark\u2019s this evening.   I felt it was meaningfully better than a 1970 Lynch Bages from last night\u2026maybe 93 vs 89-90.   I totally agree with Mark\u2019s note\u2014very savory with no signs of fading over two hours.    I bought a bunch of bottles from the same cellar on WineBid the day after Christmas of 2021.   The \u201csubterranean wine cellar\u201d description had me a bit nervous, but so far the handful of bottles I\u2019ve opened have been spectacular.  A 1979 Diamond Creek Volcanic Hill, for example, was very youthful and beautiful last week.</p>",
