        "created_at": "2023-09-30T05:37:37.617Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-Grand_Cru_Cru\" data-username=\"Mark_Thompson\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"293044\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/8e8cbc/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Mark_Thompson:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The \u201csubterranean wine cellar\u201d description had me a bit nervous, but so far the handful of bottles I\u2019ve opened have been spectacular. A 1979 Diamond Creek Volcanic Hill, for example, was</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>How were the labels?<br>\nI love wines with stained labels from humidity and little ullage.</p>",
